About me

Currently, Ive just finished my Masters and Im looking for new opportunities to develop my skills and contribute applying my knowledge to different domains of sociology, data science and network with researchers all around the world and contribute to public sociology. Research

Lately, Ive been focusing my research in basically three main objects: a) Brazilian Industrialists and their political and economic ideologies, with a special focus in 2017 Brazilian Labor Reform; b) Industrialists collective action, focusing more on their division inside their associations and social composition; and c) new methods inspired from Data Science to apply into social sciences research. All my research has been heavily influenced by Marxist and Bourdieusian researchers, and my theoretical position is to find a creative combination between these two different paradigms. Im interested in studying social classes, collective action, elites and inequalities through innovative methods and new perspectives.

Master Thesis

My master thesis focused in understanding the effects of Brazilian 2017 Labor Reform in employers unions collective action and the peculiarities of their collective action through a mixed methods approach, mixing interviews, survey, GDA and SNA.

(2021) Complexo associativo da indstria e a reforma trabalhista de 2017: um estudo do espao social dos sindicatos patronais da indstria do Paran. UFPR | Github Repo | Academia.edu | Researchgate

Bachelor Thesis

A content analysis of CNI (National Industrialists Confederation) discourse about Labor Reform in Brazil and their political and economic ideologies during the 2002-2017 timeline.

(2017) No fale em crise, trabalhe: o discurso da CNI sobre a reforma trabalhista. UFPR | Academia.edu | Researchgate

Data Science

Another pretty significant part of my activities is trying to analyze and share data for scientific divulgation purposes and provide democratic access to data while contributing to new methods of research and developing my programming skills. For now, Im relatively experienced in using R and Im also starting to develop better my Python skills. Im especially focused in Geometric Data Analysis, Social Network Analysis, Scraping, NLP, Classification and some others Machine Learning algorithms, without losing our focus in an inferential approach to statistics.
